hree Rapid Responses, explores dimensions of creativity and ethics, highlighting their connectedness. It has three parts: the first covers creative approaches to researching. The second considers concerns around research ethics and ethics more generally, and the final part addresses different ways of approaching creativity and ethics through collaboration and co-creation. The other two books focus on Response and Reassessment, and Care and Resilience. Together they help academic, applied and practitioner-researchers worldwide adapt to the new challenges COVID-19 brings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Eboni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndrews, Johanna E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBelton, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraun, Virginia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurton, Tristesse, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampbell, Lea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Naomi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColeman, Kathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrancis, Carolee Dodge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldstein, Rafael Szafir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrocott, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHealy, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiscock, Rose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1